		<div id="comment_body_64377374"><p>Looks like four questions:<br>1) Is it ethical to send a student's personal work to a third party for computer grading?<br>2) Is it ethical to give a training data set of the original student essay text, and the professor's expert grading marks to train an AI?<br>3) When will the 'business consultants' come to the university to say AI gets grading right 95% of the time, here's how to use AI and reduce your academic staff headcount by 20%<br>4) At what point do the academic graders just blanket approve the AI graded essays?</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64377374">

</div>
