	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64377656"><p>AI does some nice stuff, but it is not (yet, anyway) reliable. If a prof asks an AI for some specifics that can then be checked? No problem. Trusting the AI's results directly? No.

</p><p>I use an AI frequently, asking it to re-work a draft text that I want to send. Sometimes it finds better ways to say something. Sometimes it misunderstands the text. Sometimes it introduces errors. In the end, it's not quite as useful as asking another person for an opinion, but it's a lot more convenient. And if you asked someo<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64377656">

</div>
